tiers.name: Logic Theorist
tiers.description: Logic Theorist (1956): This was the first AI system capable of proving mathematical theorems.

tiers.name: General Problem Solver
tiers.description: General Problem Solver (1957): This was one of the first AI systems capable of reasoning and problem-solving in a general way.

tiers.name: ELIZA
tiers.description: ELIZA (1966): This was an early natural language processing program that simulated a conversation between a human and a computer.
